</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1156,969,1237]" box="[160,594,969,995]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,594,969,995]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">
Puparium 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[287,594,969,995]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">
(n = 10, 
<specimenCount box="[387,490,969,995]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625" type="female">5 female</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount box="[504,583,969,995]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625" type="male">5 male</specimenCount>
)
</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1156,969,1237]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">
Broadly elongate oval (
<figureCitation box="[437,535,1004,1029]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1511,1534]" captionTargetBox="[164,1150,145,1476]" captionTargetId="figure-1@19.[163,1153,142,1479]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp.nov., holotype puparium:(a) dorsal view; (b) antenna; (c) abdominal segments I and II, submedian pores; (d) posterior abdominal area." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000801" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000801/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">Figure 9</figureCitation>
)); female usually symmetrical; male generally asymmetrical; median and submedian area transversely pigmented on prothorax to metathorax and from abdominal segment III–VI and median anterior and posterior area (
<figureCitation box="[225,334,1108,1133]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[160,225,1537,1560]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-3@21.[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov., holotype puparium, line drawings: (a) dorsal view; (b) margin; (c) abdominal segments, sutures; (d) eye spots on prothorax; (e) vasiform orifice, posterior abdominal setae; (f) eighth abdominal setae; (g) eye spot on lateral longitudinal line. Arrow – eye spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000805/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">Figure 10</figureCitation>
)); sexually dimorphic, female puparia larger than male puparia, female 1960–2050 µm long, 1150–1400 µm wide; male 1560–1690 µm long, 840–1120 µm wide. Anterior marginal setae absent. Posterior marginal setae 30 µm long, 320– 367 µm apart.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1155,1283,1379]" box="[160,245,1283,1309]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,245,1283,1309]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">Margin</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1155,1283,1379]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">
Finely crenulate (
<figureCitation box="[355,461,1319,1344]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[160,225,1537,1560]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-3@21.[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov., holotype puparium, line drawings: (a) dorsal view; (b) margin; (c) abdominal segments, sutures; (d) eye spots on prothorax; (e) vasiform orifice, posterior abdominal setae; (f) eighth abdominal setae; (g) eye spot on lateral longitudinal line. Arrow – eye spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000805/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">Figure 10</figureCitation>
)); each crenulation accompanied by a submarginal papilla at base, 10–11 crenulations in 
<quantity box="[474,561,1354,1379]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1157,1425,1728]" box="[160,253,1425,1451]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,253,1425,1451]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">Dorsum</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1157,1425,1728]" lastBlockId="23.[160,1157,1139,1511]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="2628" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">
Granular, faintly tuberculate. Median length of cephalothorax 830–880 µm in female, 700–760 µm in male, abdomen 1130–1170 µm long in female, 860–940 µm long in male. Longitudinal moulting suture reaching margin and transverse moulting sutures reaching submargin. Pro-mesothoracic suture reaching subdorsal area, thereafter cuticle becomes unpigmented towards margin. A pair of lateral longitudinal furrows extend from cephalus to abdominal segment VII on submedian area. Eye spots present on lateral longitudinal furrows (
<figureCitation box="[659,775,1669,1694]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[160,225,1537,1560]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-3@21.[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov., holotype puparium, line drawings: (a) dorsal view; (b) margin; (c) abdominal segments, sutures; (d) eye spots on prothorax; (e) vasiform orifice, posterior abdominal setae; (f) eighth abdominal setae; (g) eye spot on lateral longitudinal line. Arrow – eye spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000805/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2625">Figure 10</figureCitation>
,g)). Four pairs of tuberculate arms, little wider than segment sutures, extending from lateral longitudinal furrows to submargin, 1 pair each in extension of abdominal segment sutures from III/IV to VI/VII. Submedian depressions present, faint. The median length of the cephalothorax was greater than that of the abdomen in both male and female puparia. The median length of the mesothorax and metathorax was 130–152 µm and 82–100 µm, respectively, in the female, and 110–130 µm and 80–100 µm, respectively, in the male. The median length of the mesothorax was greater than that of the metathorax. Median length of abdominal segments I–VIII in the female: I 95–100, II 100–102, III 107–112, IV 115–120, V 110–112, VI 100–105, VII 50–67, VIII 62–80 µm long; and in the male: I 75–85, II 75–85, III 82–95, IV 82–95, V 85–90, VI 70–82, VII 25–37, VIII 62– 75 µm (including pockets 15–20 µm long) long. The median length of abdominal segment IV is the greatest, segments III and V subequal, segment VII the smallest, segment VIII longer than VI, segment VI smaller than segments III and V and subequal to segments I and II. Median lengths of abdominal segments I–VIII: IV&gt; III = V&gt; VIII&gt; VI = II = I&gt; VII. Median area of abdominal segments II–V unpigmented in transversely oval shape (
<figureCitation box="[467,569,1278,1303]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1511,1534]" captionTargetBox="[164,1150,145,1476]" captionTargetId="figure-1@19.[163,1153,142,1479]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp.nov., holotype puparium:(a) dorsal view; (b) antenna; (c) abdominal segments I and II, submedian pores; (d) posterior abdominal area." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000801" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000801/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="2628">Figure 9</figureCitation>
), 
<figureCitation box="[598,714,1278,1303]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[160,225,1537,1560]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-3@21.[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov., holotype puparium, line drawings: (a) dorsal view; (b) margin; (c) abdominal segments, sutures; (d) eye spots on prothorax; (e) vasiform orifice, posterior abdominal setae; (f) eighth abdominal setae; (g) eye spot on lateral longitudinal line. Arrow – eye spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000805/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="2628">Figure 10</figureCitation>
(c)). Distance from posterior end of vasiform orifice and caudal tracheal pore opening area 325–360 µm in female, 262–295 µm in male. Abdominal segment sutures usually reaching subdorsal area; intersegmental sutures of abdominal segments II/III to VII/VIII extending to submargin-margin. Thoracic and caudal tracheal furrows absent. Geminate pores scattered over dorsal surface, a row on submargin, 48–50 pairs. Submarginal and subdorsal setae present. Pockets discontinuous.
</paragraph>
