<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1155,1570,1700]" box="[160,346,1570,1596]" pageId="23" pageNumber="2628">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,346,1570,1596]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="2628">Vasiform orifice</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[160,1155,1570,1700]" lastBlockId="24.[160,1155,142,237]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="2629" pageId="23" pageNumber="2628">
Subcordate (
<figureCitation box="[303,412,1606,1631]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[160,225,1537,1560]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-3@21.[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov., holotype puparium, line drawings: (a) dorsal view; (b) margin; (c) abdominal segments, sutures; (d) eye spots on prothorax; (e) vasiform orifice, posterior abdominal setae; (f) eighth abdominal setae; (g) eye spot on lateral longitudinal line. Arrow – eye spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000805/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="2628">Figure 10</figureCitation>
(e,f)), 60–70 µm long, 62–65 µm wide in female; as long as wide in male, 57–62 µm long and wide; operculum subrectangular, covering nearly half the length of the orifice, 32–35 µm long, 52–55 µm wide in female, 30–47 µm long, 42– 47 µm wide in male. Lingula exposed, not reaching beyond posterior margin of the vasiform orifice, 15–32 µm long in female, 12–20 µm long in male. A pair of setae present subapically near tip of lingula, 7 µm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,287,590]" box="[160,237,287,313]" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,237,287,313]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Venter</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,287,590]" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">
With wax glands or impression of tubercles. A pair of ventral eighth abdominal setae present, 20–30 µm long, 60–70 µm apart in female, 15–22 µm long, 40–60 µm apart in male. Antennae 145–150 µm long in female, 130–137 µm long (including keel 2 µm long) in male, extending to outside of prothoracic legs (
<figureCitation box="[716,807,426,451]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1511,1534]" captionTargetBox="[164,1150,145,1476]" captionTargetId="figure-1@19.[163,1153,142,1479]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp.nov., holotype puparium:(a) dorsal view; (b) antenna; (c) abdominal segments I and II, submedian pores; (d) posterior abdominal area." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000801" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000801/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Figure 9</figureCitation>
)). Spiracles present, first pair of spiracles located posterior of pro-mesothoracic suture and outside the lateral longitudinal furrows, second pair anterior of meso-metathoracic suture, third pair lateral of abdominal segment suture II/III and the eighth abdominal spiracle posterior lateral of vasiform orifice (
<figureCitation box="[168,273,565,590]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[160,225,1537,1560]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-3@21.[163,1153,142,1505]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov., holotype puparium, line drawings: (a) dorsal view; (b) margin; (c) abdominal segments, sutures; (d) eye spots on prothorax; (e) vasiform orifice, posterior abdominal setae; (f) eighth abdominal setae; (g) eye spot on lateral longitudinal line. Arrow – eye spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000805/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Figure 10</figureCitation>
)). Apical pads present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,640,805]" box="[160,295,640,666]" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,295,640,666]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Chaetotaxy</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,640,805]" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Anterior marginal setae absent. Posterior marginal setae 30–32 µm long, 320–367 µm apart in female; 27 µm long, 295–327 µm apart in male. Six pairs of subdorsal setae, 2 pairs each anterior and posterior area and 1 pair each on meso- and metathorax. Cephalic, first and eighth abdominal, submarginal and subdorsal setae 15–17 µm long.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,855,1227]" box="[160,377,855,881]" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,377,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Adult male (n = 1)</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,855,1227]" box="[160,315,890,915]" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">
(
<figureCitation box="[168,300,890,915]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="22.[160,225,1276,1299]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-144@22.[163,1153,142,1244]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 11. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov.: (a) adult male; (b) antenna, compound eye; (c) abdominal wax plates; (d) lingula, genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000807/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">
Figure 11 
<emphasis box="[273,300,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">–d</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
))
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,855,1227]" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">
Wings bluish green in life. Upper and lower lobes of compound eyes not connected (
<figureCitation box="[168,272,959,984]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="22.[160,225,1276,1299]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-144@22.[163,1153,142,1244]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 11. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov.: (a) adult male; (b) antenna, compound eye; (c) abdominal wax plates; (d) lingula, genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000807/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Figure 11</figureCitation>
)). Antennae 7-segmented, segment V smallest, segment VI longest, segment IV longer than V but smaller than VII. Antennal segments III–VII observed as: VI&gt; III&gt; VII&gt; IV&gt; V. Antennal segments I 27–28 µm, II 82 µm, III 125 µm, IV 28 µm, V 15 µm, VI 160 µm, VII 62–67 µm long. Four pairs of abdominal wax plates (
<figureCitation box="[741,845,1063,1088]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="22.[160,225,1276,1299]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-144@22.[163,1153,142,1244]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 11. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov.: (a) adult male; (b) antenna, compound eye; (c) abdominal wax plates; (d) lingula, genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000807/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Figure 11</figureCitation>
