<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1155,1277,1615]" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">
Wings bluish green in life. Eyes divided, upper and lower lobes of compound eyes are not connected. Antennae 7-segmented (
<figureCitation box="[636,746,1382,1407]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="23.[160,225,1028,1051]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,997]" captionTargetId="figure-192@23.[163,1153,142,997]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figure 12. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov.: (a) adult female; (b) antenna, compound eye; (c) abdominal wax plates, lingula; (d) genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000811" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000811/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Figure 12</figureCitation>
)), segment V smallest, segment VI longest, segment IV longer than V but smaller than VII, the length of antennal segments III–VII observed as: VI&gt; III&gt; VII&gt; IV&gt; V. Antennal segments I 25–28 µm, II 70–75 µm, III 115–125 µm, IV 30–38 µm, V 12–13 µm, VI 157–160 µm, VII 62–65 µm long. Two pairs of abdominal wax plates (
<figureCitation box="[433,542,1521,1546]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="23.[160,225,1028,1051]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,997]" captionTargetId="figure-192@23.[163,1153,142,997]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figure 12. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov.: (a) adult female; (b) antenna, compound eye; (c) abdominal wax plates, lingula; (d) genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000811" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000811/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Figure 12</figureCitation>
)), first pair 155 µm long, 278 µm wide; second pair 178 µm long, 275 µm wide; space between wax plates 90 µm. Lingula tongue-like (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="23.[160,225,1028,1051]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,997]" captionTargetId="figure-192@23.[163,1153,142,997]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figure 12. Aleuromarginatus martini Dubey sp. nov.: (a) adult female; (b) antenna, compound eye; (c) abdominal wax plates, lingula; (d) genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6000811" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6000811/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="2629">Figure 12</figureCitation>
)), 55 µm long. Unpaired gonopophysis with 2 pairs of long setae.
</paragraph>
